spring
------------------------------
contain dependencies to perform perticular functionality


spring boot
------------------------------
spring boot is a module that provides Rad(rapid Application Development)feature to spring framework.Spring boot is highly dependent on the starter templates and auto-connfiguration features that are very powerful 



spring-boot-starter-web =1st one have initial dependencies



pom.xml
---------
in pom.xml 

parent pom is mandatory to control version of child dependancies

<parent>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
    <version>2.5.3.RELEASE</version>
    <relativePath />
</parent>



dependencies contain dependency like

<dependencies>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-json</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-web</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-tomcat</artifactId>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>




@EnableAutoConfiguration 
----------------------------
Spring boot auto-configuration logic is implemented in spring-boot-autoconfigure.jar and works on top of @Conditional, @ConditionalOnClass and @ConditionalOnProperty annotations.
Spring boot auto-configuration scans the classpath, finds the libraries in the classpath, and then attempts to guess the best configuration for them, and finally configure all such beans.


features of spring boot 
-----------------------------
1.spring CLI-
2.spring dependency
3.starter initializer
4.Auto-configuration
5.spring actuator
6.logging and security


we need springboot because of its ->stability,based on java virtual machines,connectivity,cloud-native,flexibility,opensource



 spring                                          springboot
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
->takes time to have spring application          ->shorter way to run spring application
->manages life cycle of java                     ->need not woeey about configuring a data source
->dependency injuction framework                 ->preconfigured set of frameworks/technologies



Embedded Servers
-----------------------------------------
Spring boot applications always include tomcat as default embedded server. It enables us to run any Spring boot application from the command prompt without including any complex server infrastructure.

//in pom.xml
<dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-web</artifactId>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-tomcat</artifactId>
    </dependency>


Bootstrapping the Application
-----------------------------------------
To run spring boot application, we need to use @SpringBootApplication annotation. Behind the scenes, thatâ€™s equivalent to @Configuration, @EnableAutoConfiguration, and @ComponentScan together.


package com.example.demo;

import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;

@SpringBootApplication
public class AirlineProjectApplication {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		SpringApplication.run(AirlineProjectApplication.class, args);
		
		System.out.println("application started.....");
		
	}

}


